The USER function (of any name to choose)
give a LOGICAL VALUE to the selection criterion
of the VERTEX of coordinates (x,y,z)

This function has to have 3 parameters X Y Z in this order
and be programmed with respect to LU grammar
(cf documentation and examples of the debut menu)
to output true (1) or false (0)

All these parameters will be initialized when the function is executed
These parameters can be used or not, but have to be present
in the definition of this function.
 
EXAMPLE:
deffunc choice( x , y , z ) ;
 choice = (x>0) and (x<=5) and ( (y-2)**2 + (z-3)**2 - 4 < 0 ) ;
endfunc; 

This function choice selects the Finite Elements of which
all vertices have an abscisse x such that 0<x<=5 and (y,z) is
interne to the circle of plane yz, centred at 2,3 and of radius 2.
